    "instructions": [
        "Cook short grain white rice according to package instructions until tender and sticky.",
        "In a skillet over medium heat, cook ground beef until browned. Stir in soy sauce, sesame oil, brown sugar, garlic, ginger, and gochujang. Cook until fragrant and sauce thickens slightly. Sprinkle with 1 tsp sesame seeds.",
        "In a clean pan, drizzle a little sesame oil and cook each vegetable (carrots, bean sprouts, zucchini, mushrooms) separately for 1–2 minutes until just tender.",
        "Lightly sauté the spinach with sesame oil, or blanch for 30 seconds in boiling water and squeeze out excess moisture. Season lightly with salt if desired.",
        "In a non-stick skillet, fry the eggs sunny-side-up so the yolk stays runny.",
        "Divide rice into bowls. Arrange beef and vegetables in sections on top of the rice. Top with a fried egg. Serve with extra gochujang and garnish with sesame seeds and green onions."
